23/08/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police reported on Monday (22 August) that a Syrian national suspected of terrorism was killed and another suspect arrested in a series of gun battles in the town of Macka, northeast Turkey. 
A third man, described as a terrorist, escaped. 
Two police officers were injured. 
The police seized several AK-47 assault rifles, ammunition, hand grenades and C-4 plastic explosives. 
It was not immediately clear whether the three suspects were members of the Kurdistan Workers Party or al-Qaeda. 
Police say they were acting on a tip. 
(AFP, NTV, TurkishPress.com - 22/08/05)
